bilingual.source: That all changed in 1988 when his wife Grete found a forgotten journal at home.
bilingual.target: 这一切在1988年改变了，当时他的妻子格蕾特在家里发现了一本被遗忘的日记。

bilingual.source: She sent the journal to a newspaper, and that year Winton was seen on the British television programme That's Life.
bilingual.target: 她把日记寄给了一家报纸，那年温顿出现在英国电视节目《那就是生活》中。

list.abstract: journal（英[ˈdʒɜːnl]，美[ˈdʒɜːrnl]），英语单词，名词，意思为报纸或期刊；日记；日志。短语搭配有trade journal（行业杂志），例句为“The findings are in the journal Nature Geoscience.（这些发现发表在《自然地球科学》杂志上。）” journal名词类近义词有magazine、diary，journalist。journalism为journal的名词形式。

yingyinNormal.en: What? I didn't know you had a journal.
yingyinNormal.zh: 什么？我都不知道你有日记。

yingyinNormal.en: No. I never told anyone that. But I did write it in my journal.
yingyinNormal.zh: 并没有，我从没跟任何人说过，但我有写在我的日记里。

yingyinNormal.en: Rosie liked observing things. I'm going to read something from her journal.
yingyinNormal.zh: 罗茜喜欢观察事物，接下来我要念一段她日记里的话。

yingyinNormal.en: He never put us in any real danger. The journal is gone. She can't do anything.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他从未真的让我们有危险。日记已经销毁，她做不了什么。

yingyinNormal.en: And even if there was a journal, you don't have it in you. Make whatever assumption you want.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果日记真的存在，你也没这个种。随便你怎么想。

yingyinNormal.en: And why would I do that? I know Claire lied about the abortion, and I have the journal to prove it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我为什么要那么做呢？我知道克莱尔在流产一事上撒了谎，我也有日记作为证据。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, it's journals and research papers I wrote as a child. Aw, how cute. Is this like a diary? No, that's my potty training journal.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是我小时候写的日志与研究报告啦。真有爱这就跟日记一样吗？不是，那是我的如厕训练日志。

yingyinNormal.en: Lay the groundwork. Keep a journal of every incident of ageism you encounter.
yingyinNormal.zh: 做好前期的准备工作，记下每一件你觉得是在歧视老年人的事。

yingyinNormal.en: Because by the time you read about it in The Wall Street Journal. It's already too late.
yingyinNormal.zh: 要是等消息都上了黄花菜都凉了。

yingyinNormal.en: No. Are you a journalist now? Karen Iverson, New York Journal. And what's Karen up to? I wish I knew.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没有，你现在又是记者了？凯伦·艾弗森，纽约日报，这位凯伦要干嘛？真希望我知道。

yingyinNormal.en: Really, your potty training journal? Yeah. And forgive my crude penmanship. I didn't start typing until I was six.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不是吧，你的如厕训练日志啊。是的，字迹难看，多多包涵，我六岁之后才开始打字。

yingyinNormal.en: Sheldon, I'm the sole author on a paper being published in a distinguished journal that may change the course of my field.
yingyinNormal.zh: 谢尔顿，我以唯一作者的身份在著名期刊上发表了自己的论文，而且有可能改变我研究的这个科学领域。

yingyinNormal.en: Then one day on the treadmill, I was reading this article on Sociology Journal about how people don't start out lying to other people, they start out lying to themselve, and the things we repeat most frequently are often those lies.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有天在跑步机上，我正在读社会学杂志上的论文。上面写道，相比对他人撒谎，人们更喜欢对自己撒谎。而重复最多的那些话，通常就是谎言。
